	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Thu May 31, 2018 3:30 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: [Need Help] Megaman X2 Repro with 27C160</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The actual literal contents of the ROM control whether the cart can address two 1 MiB ROMs or one 2 MiB ROM.<br /><br />MMX2, 1.5MiB, always was on 2 ROMs.<br />MMX3, 2 MiB, was always on 1 ROM.<br /><br />The program data in MMX3 configures the CX4 to address one 2 MiB ROM. The data in MMX2 configures the CX4 to address two 1 MiB ROMs.<br /><br />On the 2DC0N board, the left one (labeled U1) is the &quot;first&quot; one. Both ROMs are connected completely in parallel, EXCEPT that they each have their own chip enable pin.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


